#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:129
msgid "General Rules - apply for all superblock formats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:131
msgid ""
"An array is ``created`` by writing appropriate superblocks to all devices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:134
msgid ""
"It is ``assembled`` by associating each of these devices with an particular "
"md virtual device.  Once it is completely assembled, it can be accessed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:138
msgid ""
"An array should be created by a user-space tool.  This will write "
"superblocks to all devices.  It will usually mark the array as ``unclean``, "
"or with some devices missing so that the kernel md driver can create "
"appropriate redundancy (copying in raid 1, parity calculation in raid 4/5)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:144
msgid ""
"When an array is assembled, it is first initialized with the SET_ARRAY_INFO "
"ioctl.  This contains, in particular, a major and minor version number.  The "
"major version number selects which superblock format is to be used.  The "
"minor number might be used to tune handling of the format, such as "
"suggesting where on each device to look for the superblock."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:151
msgid ""
"Then each device is added using the ADD_NEW_DISK ioctl.  This provides, in "
"particular, a major and minor number identifying the device to add."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:155
msgid "The array is started with the RUN_ARRAY ioctl."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:157
msgid ""
"Once started, new devices can be added.  They should have an appropriate "
"superblock written to them, and then be passed in with ADD_NEW_DISK."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:161
msgid ""
"Devices that have failed or are not yet active can be detached from an array "
"using HOT_REMOVE_DISK."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:166
msgid ""
"Specific Rules that apply to format-0 super block arrays, and arrays with no "
"superblock (non-persistent)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:168
msgid ""
"An array can be ``created`` by describing the array (level, chunksize etc) "
"in a SET_ARRAY_INFO ioctl.  This must have ``major_version==0`` and "
"``raid_disks != 0``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:172
msgid ""
"Then uninitialized devices can be added with ADD_NEW_DISK.  The structure "
"passed to ADD_NEW_DISK must specify the state of the device and its role in "
"the array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:176
msgid ""
"Once started with RUN_ARRAY, uninitialized spares can be added with "
"HOT_ADD_DISK."
msgstr ""

