msgid "array_size"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:228
msgid ""
"This can be used to artificially constrain the available space in the array "
"to be less than is actually available on the combined devices.  Writing a "
"number (in Kilobytes) which is less than the available size will set the "
"size.  Any reconfiguration of the array (e.g. adding devices) will not cause "
"the size to change. Writing the word ``default`` will cause the effective "
"size of the array to be whatever size is actually available based on "
"``level``, ``chunk_size`` and ``component_size``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:237
msgid ""
"This can be used to reduce the size of the array before reducing the number "
"of devices in a raid4/5/6, or to support external metadata formats which "
"mandate such clipping."
