msgid ""
"Active md devices for levels that support data redundancy (1,4,5,6,10) also "
"have"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:617
msgid "sync_action"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:618
msgid ""
"a text file that can be used to monitor and control the rebuild process.  It "
"contains one word which can be one of:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:622
msgid "redundancy is being recalculated after unclean shutdown or creation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:625
msgid "recover"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:626
msgid "a hot spare is being built to replace a failed/missing device"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:629
msgid "idle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:630
msgid "nothing is happening"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:631
msgid "check"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:632
msgid ""
"A full check of redundancy was requested and is happening.  This reads all "
"blocks and checks them. A repair may also happen for some raid levels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:637
msgid "repair"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:638
msgid ""
"A full check and repair is happening.  This is similar to ``resync``, but "
"was requested by the user, and the write-intent bitmap is NOT used to "
"optimise the process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:643
msgid ""
"This file is writable, and each of the strings that could be read are "
"meaningful for writing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:646
msgid ""
"``idle`` will stop an active resync/recovery etc.  There is no guarantee "
"that another resync/recovery may not be automatically started again, though "
"some event will be needed to trigger this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:651
msgid ""
"``resync`` or ``recovery`` can be used to restart the corresponding "
"operation if it was stopped with ``idle``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:654
msgid ""
"``check`` and ``repair`` will start the appropriate process providing the "
"current state is ``idle``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:657
msgid ""
"This file responds to select/poll.  Any important change in the value "
"triggers a poll event.  Sometimes the value will briefly be ``recover`` if a "
"recovery seems to be needed, but cannot be achieved. In that case, the "
"transition to ``recover`` isn't notified, but the transition away is."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:663
msgid "degraded"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:664
msgid ""
"This contains a count of the number of devices by which the arrays is "
"degraded.  So an optimal array will show ``0``.  A single failed/missing "
"drive will show ``1``, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:668
msgid ""
"This file responds to select/poll, any increase or decrease in the count of "
"missing devices will trigger an event."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:671
msgid "mismatch_count"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:672
msgid ""
"When performing ``check`` and ``repair``, and possibly when performing "
"``resync``, md will count the number of errors that are found.  The count in "
"``mismatch_cnt`` is the number of sectors that were re-written, or (for "
"``check``) would have been re-written.  As most raid levels work in units of "
"pages rather than sectors, this may be larger than the number of actual "
"errors by a factor of the number of sectors in a page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:680
msgid "bitmap_set_bits"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:681
msgid ""
"If the array has a write-intent bitmap, then writing to this attribute can "
"set bits in the bitmap, indicating that a resync would need to check the "
"corresponding blocks. Either individual numbers or start-end pairs can be "
"written.  Multiple numbers can be separated by a space."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:687
msgid ""
"Note that the numbers are ``bit`` numbers, not ``block`` numbers. They "
"should be scaled by the bitmap_chunksize."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:690
msgid "sync_speed_min, sync_speed_max"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:691
msgid ""
"This are similar to ``/proc/sys/dev/raid/speed_limit_{min,max}`` however "
"they only apply to the particular array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:694
msgid ""
"If no value has been written to these, or if the word ``system`` is written, "
"then the system-wide value is used.  If a value, in kibibytes-per-second is "
"written, then it is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:698
msgid ""
"When the files are read, they show the currently active value followed by "
"``(local)`` or ``(system)`` depending on whether it is a locally set or "
"system-wide value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:702
msgid "sync_completed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:703
msgid ""
"This shows the number of sectors that have been completed of whatever the "
"current sync_action is, followed by the number of sectors in total that "
"could need to be processed.  The two numbers are separated by a ``/``  thus "
"effectively showing one value, a fraction of the process that is complete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:709
msgid ""
"A ``select`` on this attribute will return when resync completes, when it "
"reaches the current sync_max (below) and possibly at other times."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:713
msgid "sync_speed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:714
msgid ""
"This shows the current actual speed, in K/sec, of the current sync_action.  "
"It is averaged over the last 30 seconds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:717
msgid "suspend_lo, suspend_hi"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:718
msgid ""
"The two values, given as numbers of sectors, indicate a range within the "
"array where IO will be blocked.  This is currently only supported for "
"raid4/5/6."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:722
msgid "sync_min, sync_max"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:723
msgid ""
"The two values, given as numbers of sectors, indicate a range within the "
"array where ``check``/``repair`` will operate. Must be a multiple of "
"chunk_size. When it reaches ``sync_max`` it will pause, rather than "
"complete. You can use ``select`` or ``poll`` on ``sync_completed`` to wait "
"for that number to reach sync_max.  Then you can either increase "
"``sync_max``, or can write ``idle`` to ``sync_action``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:731
msgid ""
"The value of ``max`` for ``sync_max`` effectively disables the limit. When a "
"resync is active, the value can only ever be increased, never decreased. The "
"value of ``0`` is the minimum for ``sync_min``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:738
msgid ""
"Each active md device may also have attributes specific to the personality "
"module that manages it. These are specific to the implementation of the "
"module and could change substantially if the implementation changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:743
msgid "These currently include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:745
msgid "stripe_cache_size  (currently raid5 only)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:746
msgid ""
"number of entries in the stripe cache.  This is writable, but there are "
"upper and lower limits (32768, 17).  Default is 256."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:749
msgid "strip_cache_active (currently raid5 only)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:750
msgid "number of active entries in the stripe cache"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:752
msgid "preread_bypass_threshold (currently raid5 only)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:753
msgid ""
"number of times a stripe requiring preread will be bypassed by a stripe that "
"does not require preread.  For fairness defaults to 1.  Setting this to 0 "
"disables bypass accounting and requires preread stripes to wait until all "
"full-width stripe- writes are complete.  Valid values are 0 to "
"stripe_cache_size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:759
msgid "journal_mode (currently raid5 only)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/md.rst:760
msgid ""
"The cache mode for raid5. raid5 could include an extra disk for caching. The "
"mode can be \"write-throuth\" and \"write-back\". The default is \"write-"
"through\"."
msgstr ""

